# Intuned Cookbook Project Rules

## Writing README Files

### Template README (Parent Directory)
When writing a README for a template folder (e.g., `templates/book-consultations-auth/README.md`), include:

1. **Title**: Use the template name as a heading
2. **Description**: A brief description of what the template does (taken from the TypeScript/Python sub-project READMEs)
3. **Available Versions Table**: A table linking to both TypeScript and Python implementations:
   ```markdown
   | Version | Directory | Documentation |
   |---------|-----------|---------------|
   | **TypeScript** | [`typescript/`](./typescript/) | [README](./typescript/README.md) |
   | **Python** | [`python/`](./python/) | [README](./python/README.md) |
   ```
4. **Features**: Bullet points highlighting key capabilities
5. **Learn More**: Links to relevant Intuned documentation

### Example Template README Structure
```markdown
# Template Name

Brief description of what this template does.

## Available Versions

| Version | Directory | Documentation |
|---------|-----------|---------------|
| **TypeScript** | [`typescript/`](./typescript/) | [README](./typescript/README.md) |
| **Python** | [`python/`](./python/) | [README](./python/README.md) |

## Features

- Feature 1
- Feature 2
- Feature 3

## Learn More

- [Relevant Doc 1](url)
- [Relevant Doc 2](url)
```

## Writing Recipes

### Recipe Structure
Each recipe should have its own folder under `recipes/` with:

1. **Code files named after the recipe folder** (not `handler.ts`/`handler.py`):
   - `{recipe-name}.ts` - TypeScript implementation
   - `{recipe-name}.py` - Python implementation

2. **README.md** with:
   - Brief description of what the recipe does
   - Links to the code files
   - Related SDK Methods section (if applicable) with links to SDK documentation
   - Learn More link to the recipe documentation

### Example Recipe README Structure
```markdown
# Recipe Name

Brief description of what this recipe does.

## Files

- [`recipe-name.ts`](./recipe-name.ts) - TypeScript implementation
- [`recipe-name.py`](./recipe-name.py) - Python implementation

## Related SDK Methods

- [methodName (TypeScript)](https://docs.intunedhq.com/automation-sdks/intuned-sdk/typescript/helpers/functions/methodName)
- [method_name (Python)](https://docs.intunedhq.com/automation-sdks/intuned-sdk/python/helpers/functions/method_name)

## Learn More

- [Recipe Name Recipe](https://docs.intunedhq.com/docs/01-learn/recipes/recipe-slug)
```

